.SH NAME
drm_atomic_helper_resume \- subsystem-level resume helper
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drm_atomic_helper_resume
.BI "(struct drm_device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct drm_atomic_state *state "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
DRM device
.IP "state" 12
atomic state to resume to
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Calls \fBdrm_mode_config_reset\fP to synchronize hardware and software states,
grabs all modeset locks and commits the atomic state object. This can be
used in conjunction with the \fBdrm_atomic_helper_suspend\fP helper to
implement suspend/resume for drivers that support atomic mode-setting.

See also:
\fBdrm_atomic_helper_suspend\fP
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success or a negative error code on failure.
